Israeli Officials to Meet US Envoy Ahead of Iran Talks

### English Text Summary:
An Israeli official stated that senior Israeli officials will meet with US envoy to the Middle East, Steve Wietkoff, in Rome before the second round of talks between the US and Iran scheduled for Saturday. The meeting will include Israeli Strategic Affairs Minister Ron Dermer and Mossad Director David Barnea. The Israeli Prime Minister's office defended its aggressive policy towards Iran, asserting that Israel will not allow Iran to possess nuclear weapons. Meanwhile, Iranian Foreign Minister Abbas Araghchi announced his travel to Rome for the negotiations, emphasizing that Oman remains the host for the indirect talks. He expressed concerns about conflicting statements from the US and reiterated Iran's clear stance in the negotiations.

